10:
Wh-where is this place? There's
nothing but locks! Locks, locks, locks
everywhere!
15:
Are you all right, Keyana? I don't see
a single lock anywhere!
19:
B-but, they're right there! There's
sparkly ones and chattering ones
andâ€”
21: Oh gosh, it's no use, I can't!
33:
Oh thank goodness! You were out
cold there...
38:
No doubt her sensory system
overheated. She must have
perceived the security encryptions
as individual locks, leading to a
stimulus overload.
41:
Sorry about that, missus. The
thought didn't occur to me that you
might not be compatible with this
world.
46:
No, it's okay! It just caught me off
guard, is all!
47:
My head IS still spinning a bit,
though...
51:
But it doesn't matter! If there are
locks there, you bet I'm gonna pick
'em all!
56:
Excellent, excellent! I like to see that
type of passion for the job. Droid or
no droid, I respect that.
58:
So, let's get down to business, why
don't we?
63:
You'd like me to break through a
certain android's security protocol?
66:
Yes... Unfortunately, some droids still
haven't recovered from the bug. We
hoped Dia's singing would do the
trick, but it doesn't seem to have
worked for everyone.
67:
Very rarely you get some droids
that... aren't exactly cooperative.
Such as the one you'll be going after.
71:
Did he consent to being brought
back?
74:
Beats me! I'd love to ask him, but I
doubt he'd reply.
76:
Hmm. Are you sure you're not
scheming something up again?
78:
Haha! What, still don't trust me,
Alkie-boy?
81:
If this weren't a rescue mission, I
doubt I'd have agreed to go along.
85:
Oof, day by day you're getting
colder and colder, Alk! Starting to
remind me of a certain someone.
90:
If it's against this android's wishes,
we might not be able to "unlock" him
forcefully...
94:
Perhaps.
We're almost here. Get ready.
100:
That would be him.
Can I leave the rest to you, Miss
Keyana?
106: If I don't do this right now, he...
110:
Ring, ring, ring
By the sound of my bell
I bid you open up, little lock!
118:
For runnING AWAY.
For beTRAYING YOU.
For leaVING YOU.
120:
PleaSE, I BEG YOU
Do not FORGIVE ME.
137: The hell is this all about, Regis?
141:
He's resonating with her? I have to
say, this is entirely unexpected...
151: Regis, what are you trying to do?
153:
There's no other way. I need to take
responsibility for this.
161: I'll do it. I'll open this android's lock!
163:
You ran away, right? You were
unable to fight?
164:
You left your friends behind and
couldn't help them?
167:
Ah... Ah... Ah...
Do... not... FORGIVE MEâ€”
171:
Things are different now. You don't
have to blame yourself anymore.
176: You can hear the song now, right?
178:
That means you can forgive
yourself.
Then... you can choose to fight
again. One last time.
181:
Ring, ring, ring
By the sound of my bell
I bid you open up, little lock!
187:
I am deeply sorry for all of thisâ€”I
swear to one day repay you for all
the help you've done.
192:
Don't worry! It's okay, there's nothing
to repay! I'm fine as is.
195:
Besides, I didn't do it alone. Dia's
song was able to reach the android,
after all. Make sure to thank her for
me later on, you hear?
200:
If that's over with, let's get going. If
we stay any longer Regis is likely to
get us wrapped up in another crazy
scheme of his.
206:
Now that I think about it... After we
heard that song, your lock got a little
bit looser, you know.
214:
It might be better... to lock yourself a
little bit tighter from now on.
221:
Hmm.
She doesn't seem like the type to go
along with my schemes after all.
